  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Inscribed on Ganseong Tower
  author: Heo Baek
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Mountains and waters wind through this tranquil realm,
    And as I sit, my heart grows clear and pure.
    At the fifth watch, dawn's light reaches the empty pavilion first,
    When one leaf falls, autumn's sound fills the small tower.
    The gull chasing waves knows where to rest,
    The weary bird seeking the forest finds its repose—
    Yet I, though always rushing about, what have I achieved?
    Only traveled east and west through lands unnumbered.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The 'fifth watch' refers to the final watch of the night in traditional timekeeping, around 3-5 AM, suggesting the speaker's early morning contemplation.
  - key: ''
    value: The contrast between the natural world finding rest and the speaker's fruitless journeys suggests a meditation on purposeless ambition and the wisdom found in accepting one's place.
